# React & Next.js Patterns

## Server vs Client Components
- **Default to Server Components** (no directive needed) — use for data fetching, DB queries
- Add `'use client'` only when using browser APIs, event handlers, or React hooks
- Examples: `Hello.tsx`, `CurrentCount.tsx` → server; `CounterForm.tsx`, `LocaleSwitcher.tsx` → client

## Props
- Single `props` param with inline type — **no destructuring**:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
const Card = ({ title, children }: { title: string; children: React.ReactNode }) => {}

// ✅ GOOD
const Card = (props: { title: string; children: React.ReactNode }) => {
  return <div>{props.title}{props.children}</div>;
};
```

- Use `React.ReactNode` not bare `ReactNode`

## Hooks & Optimization
- **No `useMemo` / `useCallback`** — React Compiler handles memoization in production
- **Avoid `useEffect`** whenever possible — prefer server-side logic or derived state
- Inline short event handlers; extract to named functions only when complex

## Forms & Image Upload
- Use **React Hook Form** + **Zod** for all forms
- Validate with `.safeParse()`, handle errors with `z.treeifyError()`
- After mutation, call `router.refresh()` to re-sync server data (no global state needed)
- Image upload: use `<input type="file" accept="image/jpeg,image/png,image/webp">` — validate size client-side before submitting
- Show upload progress using `XMLHttpRequest` or `fetch` with `ReadableStream` — never block UI
- Disable submit button while job is `pending` or `processing`

## Styling
- Use **Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes** — no inline styles
- No `tailwind.config.ts` — custom theme lives in `src/styles/global.css`
- `@layer` order: `theme, base, clerk, components, utilities`

## Routing
- All pages under `src/app/[locale]/`
- Use locale-aware navigation from `@/libs/i18n/I18nNavigation` (`Link`, `useRouter`, `usePathname`)
- Page files: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `route.ts` (Next.js conventions)
- `generateStaticParams` on root layout pre-generates all locale routes

## Image Display
- Use `next/image` for all images — always set `width`, `height` or `fill` + `sizes`
- Before/after comparison: render two `<img>` tags with a CSS clip-path slider (client component)
- Remove background results: wrap in `<div className="bg-[url('/checkerboard.png')]">` to show transparency
- Never render base64 image data in JSX — always use storage URLs

